{"id":459,"date":"2006-11-20T19:09:19","date_gmt":"2006-11-21T01:09:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slove_is_in_the_air.php"},"modified":"2006-11-20T19:09:19","modified_gmt":"2006-11-21T01:09:19","slug":"slove_is_in_the_air","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slove_is_in_the_air.php","title":{"rendered":"S<em>love<\/em> is in the Air"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia4.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia4.gif\" width=\"470\" height=\"200\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Recently, Slovenia, like many countries and other destinations, decided to undetake a rebranding. Unfortunately, also like many, they decided to make it a competition. Although Fundacija Brumen, the local design organization, protested, Slovenia went forward with separate competitions for the new logo and the new tagline.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"http:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/speakup\/images\/divider_hor_dotted.gif\" alt=\"divider\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The logo, designed by a Slovenian design firm called <a href=\"http:\/\/www.luksstudio.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Luks Studio<\/a>, is supposed to be Mount Triglav (the tallest mountain in Slovenia), a linden leaf (a symbol of Slovenian culture) and a heart. To me, it just looks like a flaming heart. Unless your name is<a href=\"http:\/\/littlerockpresbyterian.org\/cross\/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> Malcolm Grear<\/a>, it&#8217;s usually hard to combine more than two symbols into one cohesive and readable unit. This was not a successful attempt, especially since this a logo aimed at tourists who may not be aware of two of the three references. What I also find remarkable is that the new logo is far less friendly than the old. The icon and even the type seem too formal compared to the hand-drawn flowers breaking out of the square.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_parts.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_parts.gif\" width=\"348\" height=\"229\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/speakup\/images\/divider_hor_dotted.gif\" alt=\"divider\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The new tagline, created by an Agency called <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nuit.si\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Nuit<\/a>, is &#8220;<strong>I Feel<\/strong> S<strong>love<\/strong>nia&#8221;, with the word &#8220;Love&#8221; in Bold. I don&#8217;t think there is a graphic standard as I have seen it twice in two different typefaces, but I think it is interesting that it can not live without design meaning it doesn&#8217;t work verbally. I really like this tagline and between the logo trying to incorporate a heart and the the tagline trying the same, the tagline is much more successful. Great work. <\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia3.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia3.gif\" width=\"288\" height=\"288\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_TagHat.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_TagHat.gif\" width=\"432\" height=\"346\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/speakup\/images\/divider_hor_dotted.gif\" alt=\"divider\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Here is an alternate color version presented by Luks<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_ColorVar.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_ColorVar.gif\" width=\"239\" height=\"200\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_GreenApp1.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_GreenApp1.gif\" width=\"470\" height=\"347\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_GreenApp2.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_GreenApp2.gif\" width=\"470\" height=\"260\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Here are a few usage options presented by Luks for products and services created, made, produced or from Slovenia.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_Usage.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_Usage.gif\" width=\"470\" height=\"800\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_Usage2.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_Usage2.gif\" width=\"470\" height=\"344\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Here is an alternate sketch presented by Luks<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia_sketch.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia_sketch.gif\" width=\"239\" height=\"200\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/speakup\/images\/divider_hor_dotted.gif\" alt=\"divider\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Brandnew_Slovenia2.gif\" src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/Brandnew_Slovenia2.gif\" width=\"400\" height=\"340\" \/><\/p>\n<p>In the end, I really like the tagline and I love the energy with which Luks approached the design.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.uvi.gov.si\/eng\/slovenia\/publications\/slovenia-news\/3918\/3936\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Here&#8217;s the story:<\/a><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":14,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[9,64,26],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/459"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/14"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=459"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/459\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=459"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=459"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=459"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}